File: After a tug-of-war over viewing rights, the games will not be broadcast on SABC platforms. JOHANNESBURG - As the Absa Premiership got underway this weekend, millions of football lovers could not watch or hear their favourite teams in action.
After a tug-of-war over viewing rights, the games will not be broadcast on SABC platforms. According to a statement from the Premier Soccer League, SuperSport has accused the SABC of wanting a 96 percent discount to air the games. READ: PSL strongly objects Icasa's draft regulations This is not the first time that there have been blackouts at the SABC. In the past, Bafana Bafana matches were also affected.